## Description {#details}

This file defines a set of templates that efficiently compute a dominator tree over a generic graph.

This is used typically in LLVM for fast dominance queries on the CFG, but is fully generic w.r.t. the underlying graph types.

Unlike ADT/&#42; graph algorithms, generic dominator tree has more requirements on the graph&#39;s NodeRef. The NodeRef should be a pointer and, either NodeRef-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/basicaliasanalysis-cpp/#a1b8850f1ed44c12bc3501175a71c251c">getParent()</a> must return the parent node that is also a pointer or DomTreeNodeTraits needs to be specialized.

FIXME: Maybe GenericDomTree needs a TreeTraits, instead of GraphTraits.

<Link id="l00578" /><CodeLine lineNumber="578"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// API to update (Post)DominatorTree information based on modifications to</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00579" /><CodeLine lineNumber="579"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the CFG...</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00580" /><CodeLine lineNumber="580"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00581" /><CodeLine lineNumber="581"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Inform the dominator tree about a sequence of CFG edge insertions and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00582" /><CodeLine lineNumber="582"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// deletions and perform a batch update on the tree.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00583" /><CodeLine lineNumber="583"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00584" /><CodeLine lineNumber="584"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// This function should be used when there were multiple CFG updates after</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00585" /><CodeLine lineNumber="585"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// the last dominator tree update. It takes care of performing the updates</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00586" /><CodeLine lineNumber="586"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// in sync with the CFG and optimizes away the redundant operations that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00587" /><CodeLine lineNumber="587"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// cancel each other.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00588" /><CodeLine lineNumber="588"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The functions expects the sequence of updates to be balanced. Eg.:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00589" /><CodeLine lineNumber="589"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - &#123;&#123;Insert, A, B&#125;, &#123;Delete, A, B&#125;, &#123;Insert, A, B&#125;&#125; is fine, because</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00590" /><CodeLine lineNumber="590"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    logically it results in a single insertions.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00591" /><CodeLine lineNumber="591"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - &#123;&#123;Insert, A, B&#125;, &#123;Insert, A, B&#125;&#125; is invalid, because it doesn&#39;t make</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00592" /><CodeLine lineNumber="592"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///    sense to insert the same edge twice.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00593" /><CodeLine lineNumber="593"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00594" /><CodeLine lineNumber="594"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// What&#39;s more, the functions assumes that it&#39;s safe to ask every node in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00595" /><CodeLine lineNumber="595"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// CFG about its children and inverse children. This implies that deletions</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00596" /><CodeLine lineNumber="596"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// of CFG edges must not delete the CFG nodes before calling this function.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00597" /><CodeLine lineNumber="597"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00598" /><CodeLine lineNumber="598"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The applyUpdates function can reorder the updates and remove redundant</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00599" /><CodeLine lineNumber="599"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// ones internally (as long as it is done in a deterministic fashion). The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00600" /><CodeLine lineNumber="600"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// batch updater is also able to detect sequences of zero and exactly one</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00601" /><CodeLine lineNumber="601"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// update -- it&#39;s optimized to do less work in these cases.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00602" /><CodeLine lineNumber="602"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00603" /><CodeLine lineNumber="603"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// Note that for postdominators it automatically takes care of applying</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00604" /><CodeLine lineNumber="604"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// updates on reverse edges internally (so there&#39;s no need to swap the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00605" /><CodeLine lineNumber="605"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// From and To pointers when constructing DominatorTree::UpdateType).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00606" /><CodeLine lineNumber="606"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// The type of updates is the same for DomTreeBase&lt;T&gt; and PostDomTreeBase&lt;T&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00607" /><CodeLine lineNumber="607"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// with the same template parameter T.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00608" /><CodeLine lineNumber="608"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00609" /><CodeLine lineNumber="609"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// \\param Updates An ordered sequence of updates to perform. The current CFG</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00610" /><CodeLine lineNumber="610"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// and the reverse of these updates provides the pre-view of the CFG.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00611" /><CodeLine lineNumber="611"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00891" /><CodeLine lineNumber="891"><Highlight kind="comment">  /// verify - checks if the tree is correct. There are 3 level of verification:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00892" /><CodeLine lineNumber="892"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Full --  verifies if the tree is correct by making sure all the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00893" /><CodeLine lineNumber="893"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             properties (including the parent and the sibling property)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00894" /><CodeLine lineNumber="894"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             hold.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00895" /><CodeLine lineNumber="895"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             Takes O(N^3) time.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00896" /><CodeLine lineNumber="896"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00897" /><CodeLine lineNumber="897"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Basic -- checks if the tree is correct, but compares it to a freshly</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00898" /><CodeLine lineNumber="898"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             constructed tree instead of checking the sibling property.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00899" /><CodeLine lineNumber="899"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             Takes O(N^2) time.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00900" /><CodeLine lineNumber="900"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00901" /><CodeLine lineNumber="901"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///  - Fast  -- checks basic tree structure and compares it with a freshly</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             constructed tree.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             Takes O(N^2) time worst case, but is faster in practise (same</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><Highlight kind="comment">  ///             as tree construction).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#a1f08f2925fec05b265e540d29066b9c8"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#a1f08f2925fec05b265e540d29066b9c8">verify</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#aad6e57a3b7c184bded15b616e790781f">VerificationLevel</a> VL = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dominatortreebase/#aad6e57a3b7c184bded15b616e790781fabbd47109890259c0127154db1af26c75">VerificationLevel::Full</a>)</Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword"> const </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">&#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
